@startuml Public Access via Self-Hosted Reverse Tunnel
!theme plain
title Exposing Local k3s Service Publicly (Self-Hosted Reverse Tunnel)

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA

actor "External User\n(any network)" as user
cloud "Internet" as internet

node "VPS (Your Own Server)\npublic IP: 1.2.3.4" as vps #LightSalmon {

  package "Tunnel Server Side" as tunnelserver #White {
    component "frp server (frps)\nOR\nsshd (built-in SSH)" as frps
    component "Public Port Listener\n:80 / :443" as pubport
  }

  note right of frps
    frp option:
    install frps on VPS,
    configure to listen
    for agent connections.

    SSH option:
    sshd already installed
    on most VPS by default.
    No extra install needed.
  end note
}

node "Windows Host" as windows #LightCyan {

  node "WSL2 Ubuntu" as wsl #LightBlue {

    package "Tunnel Client Agent\n(runs on your laptop)" as tunnelagent #LightYellow {
      component "frp client (frpc)\nOR\nssh reverse tunnel" as frpc

      note right of frpc
        frp option:
        frpc -c frpc.ini

        SSH option:
        ssh -R 80:localhost:80 user@1.2.3.4
        (built-in, no extra install)
      end note
    }

    node "k3s CLUSTER (1 node)" as k3s #LightSkyBlue {

      package "Built-in Add-ons" as addons #Lavender {
        component "Klipper / ServiceLB\n(:80 on localhost)" as klipper
        component "Traefik\n(Ingress controller)" as traefik
      }

      package "Namespace: my-app" as ns #White {
        component "Ingress\n(path rule /)" as ing
        component "Service\n(ClusterIP)" as svc
        component "Pod\n(my-service:v1)" as pod1
        component "Pod\n(my-service:v1)" as pod2
      }
    }
  }
}

' --- Tunnel setup (outbound from laptop) ---
frpc -[#blue]-> frps : 1. agent initiates\noutbound connection\nto VPS on startup

' --- External traffic flow ---
user -[#red]-> internet           : http://1.2.3.4/
internet -[#red]-> pubport        : hits VPS public IP
pubport -[#red]-> frps            : VPS receives request
frps -[#red]-> frpc               : forwarded through\nthe open tunnel
frpc -[#red]-> klipper            : delivered to localhost:80

' --- Internal k3s flow ---
klipper -[#orange]-> traefik
traefik -[#orange]-> ing
ing -[#orange]-> svc
svc -[#green]-> pod1              : load balance
svc -[#green]-> pod2              : load balance

note bottom of vps
  ** VPS Requirements **
  - Any cheap VPS works
    (DigitalOcean, Vultr, AWS EC2 free tier)
  - Open port 80/443 in VPS firewall
  - frp server installed (if using frp)
    OR sshd running (if using SSH tunnel)
end note

note bottom of wsl
  ** Laptop Requirements **
  - No router config needed
  - No firewall rules needed
  - No open inbound ports
  - Just outbound connection to VPS
  - WSL2 IP changes don't matter
  - Works behind NAT
end note

note bottom of internet
  ** Comparison **
  +---------------------+----------+-----------+
  | Feature             | SSH      | frp       |
  +---------------------+----------+-----------+
  | Extra install       | None     | frps+frpc |
  | Stability           | Medium   | High      |
  | Auto-reconnect      | Manual   | Built-in  |
  | Multiple ports      | Possible | Easy      |
  | HTTPS support       | Manual   | Built-in  |
  +---------------------+----------+-----------+
end note

@enduml